    <descript>
      <abstract>Measurements of full-spectrum (i.e. 350-2500nm) canopy spectral reflectance along the Barrow, BEO NGEE-Arctic tram using the BNL manually operated instrument cart.  Spectra was collected using the manual cart with the HR-2014i instrument and a Spectralon white plate to calibrate each measurement under variable illumination conditions. Data were collected in Barrow, Alaska during the 2015-2016 period.  Additional details can be found in the resulting publications.</abstract>
    </descript>
